Package com.hemebiotech.analytics

Class CountDataFromFile

java.lang.Object
com.hemebiotech.analytics.CountDataFromFile
All Implemented Interfaces:
ISymptomCounter
public class CountDataFromFile extends Object implements ISymptomCounter
Creates an object that contains a text source file, a list of its unique distinguished lines, and a Map of these lines and their number occurrences in the source file.

    • CountDataFromFile

      public CountDataFromFile​(String pFilePath, List<String> pList)
      Constructor that instantiates a CountDataFromFile Object with a blank TreeMap a specified source file and a specified list of lines which are to be counted in this file.
      Parameters:
      pFilePath - is the relative filepath of the file to be read and counted
      pList - is a list of String compared to each line in the file you want to count. If lines and String in the list are the same then it will be counted in the map with count() method.
